50|$|In UNESCO usage, a {{recommendation}} is a formal international instrument {{accepted by the}} member states of UNESCO (UNESCO, 1981). As is generally the case with international instruments, the Recommendation is soft law, that is, {{the enforcement of the}} norms and standards within the Recommendation is through the force of moral persuasion. There is, however, potential for individual governments to translate the Recommendation into <b>hard</b> <b>law,</b> through individual legislation.|$|E
